  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6565 sitting above the max negative gamma wall at 6550 (-11.9B), dealers are currently short gamma and will amplify any directional moves by buying rallies toward 6580 resistance and aggressively selling any dips back toward the 6550-6560 negative gamma cluster. The massive negative GEX concentration between 6540-6560 creates a high-volatility zone where dealer hedging flows will accelerate price moves in either direction, while the thin positive gamma at 6580 (5.3B) provides limited upside resistance before dealers flip to selling pressure.\n\nKey levels: 6580 upside pivot where dealers turn sellers, 6550 downside magnet with maximum amplification risk, and 6540 as the lower boundary of the negative gamma minefield.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile swings with dealers pushing price away from the 6550-6560 danger zone toward either 6580 or 6540.",
